# Auto-Repackage Hook

This project has a Cursor hook at `.cursor/hooks.json` that automatically
re-packages the extension whenever an agent (or Tab) edits a packaged file.

## Triggers

The hook fires on `afterFileEdit` / `afterTabFileEdit` for paths matching:

- `src/**/*.ts`
- `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `.vscodeignore`
- `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `LICENSE`, `icon.png`

For anything else (translation JSONs, docs in subfolders, etc.) the hook
exits as a no-op.

## What it runs

`npm run package` — which chains `vscode:prepublish` → `tsc -p ./` → `vsce
package --no-dependencies`. The result is a fresh `.vsix` at the repo
root, overwriting the previous one.

## Behavior

- Runs **detached in the background**, never blocks the agent or the editor.
- **Debounced** by `I18N_SYNC_REPACKAGE_DEBOUNCE_MS` (default 1500 ms) so a
  burst of edits coalesces into a single rebuild.
- **Single-flight** via `flock` on `.cursor/hooks/.repackage.lock` so two
  packagers never run concurrently.
- All output (stdout + stderr) is appended to
  `.cursor/hooks/last-package.log`. Tail it to see the latest build:

  ```bash
  tail -f .cursor/hooks/last-package.log
  ```

## Agent guidance

- **Do not** manually run `npm run package` after editing source files — the
  hook will do it. Only run it manually when you need to inspect the build
  immediately or when working outside an agent edit (e.g. after a manual
  human edit).
- When introducing a new packaged asset, update the `in_scope` matcher in
  `.cursor/hooks/repackage.sh` so edits to it also trigger a repackage.
- To temporarily disable: rename `.cursor/hooks.json` to
  `.cursor/hooks.json.disabled` and reload Cursor.
